stickersOnItem: [{'stickerType': 4, 'stickerText': ['This female albino Darwin Carpet Python laid her eggs while I was away. ', 'Unfortunately she didn’t coil some of the eggs in after she laid them. ', 'Since it’s only been a day or two, I am hopeful that the eggs are still viable. ', 'She is curious to what I’m doing. ', 'She doesn’t want to let her babies go and she is coiled up tight. ', 'She is being such a good girl. Not once did she try to bite me. ', 'Snakes are maternal animals and will maternally incubate their eggs if left with her. ', 'Eventually we are able to get a big bunch of her eggs off her. ', 'The eggs get put into a large tub with a tray to suspend them over damp vermiculite. ', 'When we put mum back into her tub, we check her tummy to make sure she laid all her eggs. ', 'Her belly is all empty. ', 'Good job mamma 💖', '14 beautiful eggs. ']}, {'stickerType': 9, 'stickerText': ['Snake Eggs ']}]
